718292f-a.text:
Central Park: The Sheridan Monument in a small square at the southeastern corner of the Park, that technically is called Grand Army Plaza. The photographer is viewing northeastward to show buildings on the east side of Fifth Ave., at 60th Street.
1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.

709079f-a.text:
Fifth Avenue, at the S.E. corner of E. 60th Street as viewed eastward from the Grand Army Plaza. The 1O story corner building bears numbers '86-7, while adjoining same is a studio structure bearing No. 784-5. To the left appears a portion of the Metropolitan Club occupying a site at the N.E. corner. Also shown is an eastward view of the south side of E. 60th Street from Fifth to Madison Avenues.
April 23, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
